HEADWORD: Kinesiatrics
<hw>Kin`e*si*at"rics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. (<?/)
motion (fr. <grk>kinei^n</grk> to move) + (<?/) pertaining to medicine,
fr. (<?/) a physician.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A mode of treating
disease by appropriate muscular movements; -- also termed
<altname>kinesitherapy</altname>, <altname>kinesipathy</altname>,
<altname>lingism</altname>, and the <altname>movement
cure</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
